The paper discusses querying graph structured data on the web, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a new approach for clustering search results, which involves using language models and JS divergence as a distance measure, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses user experience, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.SI).
